<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910122-0073</DOCNO><DOCID>910122-0073.</DOCID><HL>   Bush Gives Tax Exemption   To Troops in Combat Zone</HL><DATE>01/22/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3</SO><CO>   MDEST TAXES</CO><GV>EXECUTIVE (EXE)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><LP>   WASHINGTON -- President Bush gave a tax exemption tomilitary personnel in the Persian Gulf area.   Mr. Bush formally declared the Arabian Peninsula and itssurrounding waters a combat zone, which exempts enlistedpersonnel from income tax on their military pay and freesofficers from tax on the first $500 a month of their pay.</LP><TEXT>   Military personnel in the combat zone also will have moretime to file their tax returns. The forms won't be due untilat least 180 days after they leave the area.</TEXT></DOC>